{"parentUuid":"256daaaf-d045-4f49-8e41-b093208348dd","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Administrator","sessionId":"c8e03966-bce7-4e19-8921-113557d74d75","version":"2.1.50","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"cozy-marinating-galaxy","type":"progress","data":{"message":{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M7irFUAAT9UA9DoSLnWrb2","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"C# DXGI Desktop Duplication API example SharpDX alternative .NET 8 2025\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"desktop-duplication-net/DesktopDuplication/DesktopDuplicator.cs at master · jasonpang/desktop-duplication-net\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/jasonpang/desktop-duplication-net/blob/master/DesktopDuplication/DesktopDuplicator.cs\"},{\"title\":\"Desktop Duplication API - Win32 apps | Microsoft Learn\",\"url\":\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/direct3ddxgi/desktop-dup-api\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - jasonpang/desktop-duplication-net: Windows 8 Desktop Duplication API for C# and .NET.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/jasonpang/desktop-duplication-net\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - lepoco/dxnet: DX .NET, a fork of SharpDX, is free software allowing the development of high performance game, 2D and 3D graphics rendering as well as realtime sound application.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/lepoco/dxnet\"},{\"title\":\"NuGet Gallery | DesktopDuplication 1.0.1\",\"url\":\"https://www.nuget.org/packages/DesktopDuplication\"},{\"title\":\"C# DirectX API Face-off: SlimDX vs SharpDX – Which should you choose? | Katy's Code\",\"url\":\"https://katyscode.wordpress.com/2013/08/24/c-directx-api-face-off-slimdx-vs-sharpdx-which-should-you-choose/\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - Shehryar/Duplicator: Screen Capture and Video Recording C# samples\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/Shehryar/Duplicator\"},{\"title\":\"Desktop Duplication Sample · Issue #42 · amerkoleci/Vortice.Windows\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/amerkoleci/Vortice.Windows/issues/42\"},{\"title\":\"Desktop Duplication - Windows drivers | Microsoft Learn\",\"url\":\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-hardware/drivers/display/desktop-duplication-api\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - atcarter714/DXSharp: A modern .NET 8 binding for DirectX\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/atcarter714/DXSharp\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here are some useful resources for C# DXGI Desktop Duplication API with alternatives to SharpDX for .NET 8:\n\n## Desktop Duplication API Examples\n\nThere's a Windows 8 Desktop Duplication API implementation for C# and .NET available at the jasonpang/desktop-duplication-net GitHub repository, which includes practical examples of using the API.\n\n## SharpDX Alternatives for .NET 8\n\n1. **DX .NET**: DX .NET is a fork of SharpDX that is free software allowing the development of high performance game, 2D and 3D graphics rendering as well as realtime sound application. It provides a DXNET.DXGI Assembly for DirectX - DXGI managed API.\n\n2. **DXSharp**: DXSharp is a lightweight C# wrapper for the DirectX 12 API, designed specifically for .NET 8, providing high-performance access to DirectX for real-time 3D applications, game engines, and more. With the discontinuation of SharpDX, SlimDX, XNA, and Managed DirectX, more contemporary DirectX 12 solutions are desired in the .NET ecosystem.\n\n3. **Vortice.Windows**: Vortice.Windows is another option that users have explored as an alternative to SharpDX for implementing Desktop Duplication API.\n\n## Additional Resources\n\nThere's also a Duplicator sample project that uses SharpDX exclusively for DirectX, DXGI, Direct2D and Media Foundation interop, with the Windows Desktop Duplication API for desktop duplication.\n\nThese options provide modern alternatives for working with the Desktop Duplication API in .NET 8 environments.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"e8f1ba1f-8d1d-4984-af3a-cada564814bb","timestamp":"2026-02-21T11:59:31.823Z"},"normalizedMessages":[],"type":"agent_progress","prompt":"Phase 1 MVP 설계를 해줘. 커스텀 원격 데스크톱 솔루션의 LAN 화면 공유 MVP.\n\n## 배경\n- 설비 PC에 원격 접속하여 화면 공유/제어하는 솔루션\n- TeamViewer/AnyDesk 대체 자체 솔루션\n- MCP/AI Agent 기능은 현재 범위에서 제외\n\n## 확정 사항\n- C# .NET 8 (LTS)\n- Agent: 트레이 앱 (Windows Service 아님 — DXGI가 Session 0에서 안 됨)\n- Client: WinForms\n- DXGI Desktop Duplication API로 화면 캡처\n- Win32 SendInput으로 입력 시뮬레이션\n- Raw TCP + 커스텀 프로토콜 (VNC/RFB 아님)\n- JPEG 압축\n- LAN 기본 FPS: 15\n- 인증: 챌린지-리스펀스 (nonce + SHA256)\n- 프로젝트 경로: C:\\Users\\Administrator\\Desktop\\DAEHYUN_PRIVATE\\RemoteControl\n\n## 프로젝트 구조 (Phase 1 범위)\n- RemoteDesktop.Common — 공통 프로토콜, 모델, 직렬화\n- RemoteDesktop.Agent — 설비 PC 트레이 앱 (화면 캡처 + TCP 리스너 + 입력 시뮬)\n- RemoteDesktop.Client — WinForms 뷰어 (원격 화면 표시 + 마우스/키보드 전송)\n\n## 패킷 구조\n[4 byte 패킷 길이] + [1 byte 패킷 타입] + [N byte 페이로드]\n\n## Phase 1 패킷 (MVP)\n| 코드 | 패킷명 | 방향 | 설명 |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 0x01 | AUTH_REQUEST | Client → Agent | 접속 인증 요청 |\n| 0x02 | AUTH_RESPONSE | Agent → Client | 인증 결과 |\n| 0x03 | AUTH_CHALLENGE | Agent → Client | 챌린지 nonce 전송 |\n| 0x10 | SCREEN_FULL | Agent → Client | 전체 화면 프레임 (JPEG) |\n| 0x20 | MOUSE_MOVE | Client → Agent | 마우스 이동 |\n| 0x21 | MOUSE_CLICK | Client → Agent | 마우스 클릭 |\n| 0x22 | MOUSE_SCROLL | Client → Agent | 마우스 스크롤 |\n| 0x30 | KEY_EVENT | Client → Agent | 키보드 입력 |\n| 0xF0 | HEARTBEAT | 양방향 | 연결 유지 (5초) |\n\n## 설계 요청\n다음을 포함한 상세 구현 계획을 만들어줘:\n\n1. **솔루션 구조**: 프로젝트별 폴더/파일 구조\n2. **Common 라이브러리**: 패킷 정의, 직렬화/역직렬화, TCP 헬퍼\n3. **Agent 아키텍처**: \n   - DXGI Desktop Duplication 화면 캡처 (15fps 타이머)\n   - TCP 리스너 (포트 5900)\n   - 인증 처리 (챌린지-리스펀스)\n   - JPEG 인코딩\n   - SendInput 입력 시뮬레이션\n   - 트레이 앱 구조 (NotifyIcon)\n4. **Client 아키텍처**:\n   - 접속 폼 (IP/비밀번호 입력)\n   - 뷰어 폼 (PictureBox or Panel + 더블버퍼링)\n   - 마우스/키보드 이벤트 캡처 및 전송\n   - 화면 비율 맞춤 (스케일링)\n\n각 파일의 주요 클래스/메서드 시그니처까지 포함해줘. 구현 순서도 제시해줘.\n","agentId":"a310437eca56b979c"},"toolUseID":"agent_msg_01VJQGDdge9eLuUbopGXRjpY","parentToolUseID":"toolu_01MGohPE7wp5TVS4dLtXj5ua","uuid":"ee2851c7-214f-45ef-b8ab-458e8bcbc669","timestamp":"2026-02-21T11:59:31.824Z"}
{"parentUuid":"ee2851c7-214f-45ef-b8ab-458e8bcbc669","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Administrator","sessionId":"c8e03966-bce7-4e19-8921-113557d74d75","version":"2.1.50","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"cozy-marinating-galaxy","type":"progress","data":{"message":{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01U8LE4y1kjMqsk3VCdVR4rw","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"C# SendInput P/Invoke mouse keyboard simulation .NET 8\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"GitHub - michaelnoonan/inputsimulator: Windows Input Simulator (C# SendInput Wrapper - Simulate Keyboard and Mouse)\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/michaelnoonan/inputsimulator\"},{\"title\":\"Simulate keyboard events - Windows Forms | Microsoft Learn\",\"url\":\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/desktop/winforms/input-keyboard/how-to-simulate-events\"},{\"title\":\"How to simulate mouse events - Windows Forms | Microsoft Learn\",\"url\":\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/desktop/winforms/input-mouse/how-to-simulate-events\"},{\"title\":\"NuGet Gallery | H.InputSimulator 1.5.0\",\"url\":\"https://www.nuget.org/packages/H.InputSimulator\"},{\"title\":\".net - how simulate keyboard and mouse whilst in ... | DaniWeb\",\"url\":\"https://www.daniweb.com/programming/software-development/threads/362589/how-simulate-keyboard-and-mouse-whilst-in-game\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - HossamElwahsh/AvaloniaInputSimulator: Windows Input Simulator (C# SendInput Wrapper - Simulate Keyboard and Mouse) works with Avalonia\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/HossamElwahsh/AvaloniaInputSimulator\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - MediatedCommunications/WindowsInput: Capture and Simulate Keyboard and Mouse Input\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/MediatedCommunications/WindowsInput\"},{\"title\":\"How to: Simulate Mouse and Keyboard Events in Code - Windows Forms .NET Framework | Microsoft Learn\",\"url\":\"https://learn.microsoft.com/sl-si/dotnet/desktop/winforms/how-to-simulate-mouse-and-keyboard-events-in-code?view=netframeworkdesktop-4.8\"},{\"title\":\"Sending Keystrokes to Other Apps with Windows API and C#\",\"url\":\"https://dzone.com/articles/sending-keys-other-apps\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - yingDev/inputsimulator: Windows Input Simulator (C# SendInput Wrapper - Simulate Keyboard and Mouse)\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/yingDev/inputsimulator\"}]\n\nHere are the search results for C# SendInput P/Invoke mouse and keyboard simulation with .NET 8:\n\n## Key Findings\n\n**Libraries & Frameworks:**\n\nThe Windows Input Simulator provides a simple .NET (C#) interface to simulate Keyboard or Mouse input using the Win32 SendInput method.\n\nH.InputSimulator supports .NET Standard 2.0+, .Net Framework 4.6.2 and .Net 8+. This makes it a good option for .NET 8 development.\n\n**Official Microsoft Resources:**\n\nWindows provides methods you can call to simulate mouse movements and clicks such as User32.dll SendInput and User32.dll SetCursorPos.\n\n**P/Invoke Implementation Details:**\n\nIn a C# application, the SendInput declaration using P/Invoke would look like: `[DllImport(\"user32.dll\", SetLastError = true)] public static extern uint SendInput(uint nInputs, INPUT[] pInputs, int cbSize);`\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\nSendInput is subject to UIPI: your tool cannot inject into a higher-integrity target. If the game runs elevated, run your tool elevated or the injection will silently fail.\n\nGames often ignore virtual-key events; they tend to honor hardware scan codes. When you build your input, set KEYEVENTF_SCANCODE (and KEYEVENTF_EXTENDEDKEY for extended keys) so the game sees a physical press.\n\nSeveral open-source wrappers are available on GitHub and NuGet if you prefer not to implement P/Invoke directly.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"9c7718d3-7295-4719-ac17-faadddff55c2","timestamp":"2026-02-21T11:59:32.311Z"},"normalizedMessages":[],"type